in the Functions folder we have
- sim_model_function.R is the function that creates simulations, beta and true outcomes
- estimation_function.R is the function we use to estimate the coefficients of SMAC and other methods
- calculation_function.R is the function we use to retrieve the predicted counterfactual outcomes for the treated units
- point_estimate_function.R is the function that calculates the MSE and bias from predictions for the treated units
- ci_function is the function that calculates the confidence intervals from predictions for the treated units
- ci_function is the function that calculates the coverage for the treated units


For the postestimation we have 

- wrap.R which stores into a list all the simulations for the 200 replications and the predicted outcomes, 
  MSE and bias, confidence intervals and coverage 

